Angular TemplateRef ViewContainerRef

https://indepth.dev/posts/1052/exploring-angular-dom-manipulation-techniques-using-viewcontainerref
In the Angular world a View is a fundamental building block of the application UI. It is the smallest grouping of elements which are created and destroyed together. Angular philosophy encourages developers to see the UI as a composition of Views, not as a tree of standalone HTML tags.

Angular supports two types of views:

Embedded Views which are linked to a Template
Host Views which are linked to a Component



shortcut comes in the form of two directives: 
ngTemplateOutlet 
ngComponentOutlet



